{% comment %}
  CLASSNAME MERGE (Shopify version of `cn()`)

  In React, `cn()` merges conditional class names using clsx + tailwind-merge.
  In Liquid, we achieve the same via:
  - Conditional string concatenation
  - Liquid filters and `if` logic

  Usage:
  {% render 'utils-cn',
    base: 'bg-black text-white',
    extra: class_variable,
    condition: product.available
  %}
{% endcomment %}

{% assign base = base | default: '' %}
{% assign extra = extra | default: '' %}
{% assign condition = condition | default: true %}

{% if condition %}
  {{ base | append: ' ' | append: extra | strip }}
{% else %}
  {{ base | strip }}
{% endif %}
